<TITLE> Govt transfers more civil servants </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 2 (bdnews24.com)  The government has made changes to eleven administrative posts, the establishment ministry said in a statement on Tuesday. Officer on special duty (OSD) deputy secretary at the establishment ministry Nasima Begum has been made director of BIAM Foundation. Abdul Quiyum Miah, deputy secretary at the ministry of Chittagong Hill Tracts Affairs, has been appointed director of Implementation Monitoring and Evaluation Division on deputation. Muktijoddha Kalyan Trust director Md Sayedur Rahman has been appointed director of Bangladesh Road Transport Corporation (BRTC). Deputy secretary Aminul Islam, who had been transferrd to defence ministry, has been made director of the Directorate of Family Planning. Abdus Salam Miah, who had been ordered to join the directorate, has been sent Bangladesh Postal Department as its director. Establishment ministry deputy secretary Amir Hossain has been made additional director at Bangladesh Film Development Corporation on deputation. OSD deputy secretary Nasrin Ara Surat, previously moved to the agriculture ministry, has been transferred to the CHT Affairs ministry. BRTC director Nurul Islam has been made deputy secretary at the defence ministry. Deputy secretary Navas Chandra Mondol, currently deputy director of BCS Administrative Academy, has been transferred to the establishment ministry. Senior assistant secretary Syeda Nawshin Pornini has been sent to BCS Administrative Academy as deputy secretary on deputation to replace senior assistant secretary Begum Sahana. bdne
